`ReflectionUtils` is annotated with `@API(status = INTERNAL)`. Thus, it's an internal class and shouldn't be used by third-party projects like Dropwizard. That being said, I see @joschi has already [updated](https://github.com/dropwizard/dropwizard/pull/9154) Dropwizard's JUnit dependency to 5.11.0 which caused it to be recompiled now using the `ReflectionUtils.makeAccessible(Field)` method rather than the no longer existing `ReflectionUtils.makeAccessible(AccessibleObject)` one. I think the quickest way to resolve the issue is to release a patch version of Dropwizard.

@joschi Do you think that would be feasible?

To avoid this in the future, we should introduce a `makeAccessible(Field)` method in `ReflectionSupport` which is intended to be used by third parties.
